Job description
  About the Company
 SGITS empowers corporations and individuals around the globe with the ability to go green and do their part in limiting the environment from further climate change.
 We can help support and contribute to more sustainable and renewable energy sources by purchasing renewable energy certificates (RECs) using our reliable trading platform powered by cutting-edge blockchain technology and artificial intelligence.
 SGITS provides a TRUSTED end-to-end service for our clients, from RECs qualified by the global registry, buyers-sellers fast matching, post-sale ownership verification, and easy RECs retirement to trading fraud prevention.
  Responsibilities
 As a Senior Software Engineer, your key responsibilities include:
  Developing innovative system management solutions and automation tools;
  Self-managed, able to come up solution for technical problem, you are usually handle end-to-end for a feature or even a product;
  Providing support for service operations also maintaining and enhancing the existing toolset;
  Supporting automation initiatives in the production environment;
Your skills and experience
  On Technical Side, we’re looking for a teammate with:
  Absolute understanding of C# and .NET Core framework.
  Proficiency with HTML, CSS, JavaScript, jQuery, and the latest version of ECMAScript. You may be familiar with state-of-the-art front end library or frameworks like VueJs, ReactJs, React Native;
  Solid experience writing unit tests;
  Experience working with cloud services, in particular Azure cloud that we’re in love with;
  Working experience with Git;
  Exposure to Docker, Kubernetes, and microservices will be an added bonus;
  Experience in developing RESTful API;
  Focus on efficiency, user experience, and process improvement;
  Experience with working with RDBMS such as SQL Server or MySQL;
  Experience and Education
  Bachelor’s degree in computer programming, computer science, or a related field; We’d love to have you from 4 years of experience in software development both front-end and back-end, but absolutely open to talents;
  Ability to work independently or with a group with good time management skills;
  Demonstrate your problem-solving capabilities by effectively managing multiple projects concurrently, leveraging your strong analytical skills;
  Self-motivated and an A team player; You’re expected to be comfortable working in a team, treating your peers with respect and dignity, willing to receive & give feedback to grow both personally and as an engineer.
  Ability to communicate effectively in English;
Why you'll love working here
   Performance Management – Assess based on the Company's Performance Management Plan annually;
   18 days off  in a calendar year;
   Performance review twice a year;
   Meal allowance
   Great allowances (parking, birthday, happy hours, promotion…);
   Outing/team-building activities (company trip, sports club…);
   Monthly Gross Salary will be 100% for insurance and income tax purposes;
   Probation Period: Two (2) Months with 100% monthly gross salary;
   Other benefits as stated in Vietnamese Labor Law;
   Training opportunity: both technical and soft skills to develop your career path;
